because there are just too many things to remember https://cloud-fundis.github.io/lessons/jq/lesson-n/ -<p>After all your learnings and this series, we&rsquo;re trying to get to understand and write <em>jq</em> like the one below. It&rsquo;s a culmination of our learnings:</p>

<pre><code>jq 'def dotkeys:
	def stringify: map(tostring) | join(&quot;.&quot;);
	. as $in
	| reduce paths(scalars) as $p (null;
		($in|getpath($p)) as $v
		| setpath([$p|stringify]; $v));
	def chain(key):
	.[key] |= dotkeys ;
   chain(&quot;AParticularNestedKey&quot;)'
</code></pre>

<p>Yup, this looks terrible, even to me. So I&rsquo;m on a quest and hopefully this&rsquo;ll make more sense as these lessons progress.</p>

<p>But we&rsquo;re not there yet.</p>

<p>Thanks @doug for this little bit of chicken-scratch.</p>
